<h4 id="then-i-need-to-plot-the-data">Then, I need to plot the data</h4>

<p><strong>Let’s see an overview</strong></p>

<pre><code class="language-{r}">  ggplot(sc_companies, 
         aes(x = date, y = close, color = symbol)) + 
    geom_line(size=1) +
    labs(title = "Semiconductor Stock Price",
         subtitle = 'A comparation between companies',
         x = 'Date',
         y =  "Close Price") +
    theme_minimal() +
    scale_color_brewer(palette = "Dark2") 
</code></pre>

<p><img src="/img/semiconductores/semiconductorstockprice.png" alt="Index" /></p>

<p><strong>Let’s wrap for a better view.</strong></p>

